                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/159</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-26T15:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 26, 1917—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister of Foreign Affairs <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government informs me
                    their agent, Washington, Fernandez Guardia to be withdrawn June 1 in the absence
                    of recognition.</p>
                <p>Joaquin Tinoco leaving 29th, steamship <hi rend="italic">Calamares</hi> for New
                    York to continue efforts in that city.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
